operating loss carryforwards (nols) were acquired in previous business
combinations. during the fourth quarter of 2005, these nols were deemed to be
more likely than not to be realized and accordingly the valuation allowances
were reversed against the related goodwill that was recognized at the time of
the acquisitions.
